Telangana Pradesh Congress Committee Working President Mallu Bhatti Vikramarka on Thursday urged the Governor ESL Narasimhan to call for all relevant documents pertaining to Mission Bhagiratha to examine alleged irregularities in awarding tenders to certain firms.While complimenting the Governor for field level visit to inspect the progress of Mission Bhagiratha works that entails potable drinking water to each household in Telangana, the TPCC Working President wondered why the alleged irregularities in the ambitious project did not come to his notice. He said the Governor after going through the tenders invited for the works should direct the Government to stop all ongoing works. He said a closer look at the works would reveal the alleged corruption involved in the scheme.KCR flayedMr. Bhatti regretted that the Chief Minister K.Chandrasekhar Rao did not have the time to condole the death of Dalit research scholar Rohith Vemula. He said when the issue of the unfortunate suicide had kicked up a major row across the country, the Chief Minister did not bother even to react.Congress asks Governor to recall the documents to check irregularities in awarding tenders